results.source_text: The 62-year-old female with a history of type 2 diabetes presented with chest pain and shortness of breath. Ardiaca valuation including an ECG showed a st-segment elevation. Tropanin levels were elevated at 5.2 NG-slash NL. The cardiologist diagnosed and acute mycardial infarction and performed emergency PCI percutaneous coronary intervention. The patient was started on aspirin, clopidoprol, an adorvastatin, and was advised cardiac rehabilitation.
